0.name: Desert Eagle
0.desc: As expensive as it is powerful, the Desert Eagle is an iconic pistol that is difficult to master but surprisingly accurate at long range.

1.name: Dual Berettas
1.desc: Firing two large-mag Berettas at once will lower accuracy and increase load times. On the bright side, you'll get to fire two large-mag Berettas at once.

2.name: Five-SeveN
2.desc: Highly accurate and armor-piercing, the pricy Five-Seven is a slow-loader that compensates with a generous 20-round magazine and forgiving recoil.

3.name: Glock-18
3.desc: The Glock 18 is a serviceable first-round pistol that works best against unarmored opponents and is capable of firing three-round bursts.

4.name: AK-47
4.desc: Powerful and reliable, the AK-47 is one of the most popular assault rifles in the world. It is most deadly in short, controlled bursts of fire.

5.name: AUG
5.desc: Powerful and accurate, the AUG scoped assault rifle compensates for its long reload times with low spread and a high rate of fire.

6.name: AWP
6.desc: High risk and high reward, the infamous AWP is recognizable by its signature report and one-shot, one-kill policy.

7.name: FAMAS
7.desc: A cheap option for cash-strapped players, the FAMAS effectively fills the niche between more expensive rifles and the less-effective SMGs.

8.name: G3SG1
8.desc: The pricy G3SG1 lowers movement speed considerably but compensates with a higher rate of fire than other sniper rifles.

9.name: Galil AR
9.desc: A less expensive option among the terrorist-exclusive assault rifles, the Galil AR is a serviceable weapon in medium to long-range combat.

10.name: M249
10.desc: A strong open-area LMG, the M249 is the perfect choice for players willing to trade a slow fire rate for increased accuracy and a high ammo capacity.

11.name: M4A4
11.desc: More accurate but less damaging than its AK-47 counterpart, the M4A4 is the full-auto assault rifle of choice for CTs.

12.name: MAC-10
12.desc: Essentially a box that bullets come out of, the MAC-10 SMG boasts a high rate of fire, with poor spread accuracy and high recoil as trade-offs.

13.name: P90
13.desc: Easily recognizable for its unique bullpup design, the P90 is a great weapon to shoot on the move due to its high-capacity magazine and low recoil.

14.name: MP5-SD
14.desc: Often imitated but never equaled, the iconic MP5 is perhaps the most versatile and popular SMG in the world. This SD variant features an integrated silencer, making an already formidable weapon whisper-quiet.

15.name: UMP-45
15.desc: The misunderstood middle child of the SMG family, the UMP45's small magazine is the only drawback to an otherwise versatile close-quarters automatic.

16.name: XM1014
16.desc: The XM1014 is a powerful fully automatic shotgun that justifies its heftier price tag with the ability to paint a room with lead fast.

17.name: PP-Bizon
17.desc: The Bizon SMG is low-damage, but offers a uniquely designed high-capacity drum magazine that reloads quickly.

18.name: MAG-7
18.desc: The CT-exclusive Mag-7 delivers a devastating amount of damage at close range. Its rapid magazine-style reloads make it a great tactical choice.

19.name: Negev
19.desc: The Negev is a beast that can keep the enemy at bay with its pin-point supressive fire, provided you have the luxury of time to gain control over it.

20.name: Sawed-Off
20.desc: The classic Sawed-Off deals very heavy close-range damage, but with its low accuracy, high spread and slow rate of fire, you'd better kill what you hit.

21.name: Tec-9
21.desc: An ideal pistol for the Terrorist on the move, the Tec-9 is lethal in close quarters and features a high magazine capacity.

22.name: P2000
22.desc: Accurate and controllable, the German-made P2000 is a serviceable first-round pistol that works best against unarmored opponents.

23.name: MP7
23.desc: Versatile but expensive, the German-made MP7 SMG is the perfect choice for high-impact close-range combat.

24.name: MP9
24.desc: Manufactured in Switzerland, the cutting-edge MP9 SMG is an ergonomic polymer weapon favored by private security firms.

25.name: Nova
25.desc: The Nova's rock-bottom price tag makes it a great ambush weapon for a cash-strapped team.

26.name: P250
26.desc: A low-recoil firearm with a high rate of fire, the P250 is a relatively inexpensive choice against armored opponents.

27.name: SCAR-20
27.desc: The SCAR-20 is a semi-automatic sniper rifle that trades a high rate of fire and powerful long-distance damage for sluggish movement speed and big price tag.

28.name: SG 553
28.desc: The terrorist-exclusive SG553 is a premium scoped alternative to the AK47 for effective long-range engagement.

29.name: SSG 08
29.desc: The SSG08 bolt-action is a low-damage but very cost-effective sniper rifle, making it a smart choice for early-round long-range marksmanship.

30.name: C4 Explosive
30.desc: Stable and resistant to most physical shocks, this improvised plastic explosive has a detonation velocity of over 8,000 meters per second when ignited.

31.name: M4A1-S
31.desc: With a smaller magazine than its unmuffled counterpart, the silenced M4A1 provides quieter shots with less recoil and better accuracy.

32.name: USP-S
32.desc: A fan favorite from Counter-Strike Source, the Silenced USP Pistol has a detachable silencer that gives shots less recoil while suppressing attention-getting noise.

33.name: CZ75-Auto
33.desc: A fully automatic variant of the CZ75, the CZ75-Auto is the ideal short-term choice for turning the tables and gaining your opponents weapon. But with very little ammo in the magazine, strong trigger discipline is required.

34.name: R8 Revolver
34.desc: The R8 Revolver delivers a highly accurate and powerful round at the expense of a lengthy trigger-pull. Firing rapidly by fanning the hammer may be the best option when point-blank stopping power is required.

35.name: Knife
35.desc: Quiet and always available, the knife has a fast, low-damage primary attack and a slow, high-damage secondary attack. A backstab will earn quiet players an instant kill.

36.name: Knife
36.desc: Quiet and always available, the knife has a fast, low-damage primary attack and a slow, high-damage secondary attack. A backstab will earn quiet players an instant kill.

37.name: Bayonet
37.desc: Relatively unchanged in its design since World War II, the bayonet still retains a place in modern military strategy. Bayonet charges have continued to be effective as recently as the second Gulf War and the war in Afghanistan.

38.name: Classic Knife
38.desc: A classic of the Counter-Strike series, the edge of this knife is press-fit Stellite perfectly held in place due to its precise fit with the titanium on the blade's cheek and spine. The handle is fossilized mastodon ivory held in a carbon fibre pocket.

39.name: Flip Knife
39.desc: Flip knives sport a Persian-style back-swept blade with an acute point.  While the point itself may be fragile, the overall design of the flip knife's design is surprisingly durable.

40.name: Gut Knife
40.desc: The most notable feature of a gut knife is the gut hook on the spine of the blade.  Originally popularized as an aid for field dressing game, the gut hook is also effective at  cutting through fibrous materials like rope, webbing, or safety belts with ease.

41.name: Karambit
41.desc: With its curved blade mimicking a tiger's claw, the karambit was developed as part of the southeast Asian martial discipline of silat. The knife is typically used with a reverse grip, with the finger ring on the index finger.

42.name: M9 Bayonet
42.desc: This is the M-9 bayonet.  Originally intended to be mounted on a rifle, it is also well suited to close-quarters combat.

43.name: Huntsman Knife
43.desc: A knife designed for modern tactical uses, the blade is well suited for a range of both combat and utilitarian needs.  The unique Tanto point allows for maximum penetration through even the toughest of surfaces.

44.name: Falchion Knife
44.desc: A modern homage to a falchion sword, this clip point blade has a curved edge.

45.name: Bowie Knife
45.desc: This full-tang sawback Bowie knife is designed for heavy use in brutal survival situations.

46.name: Butterfly Knife
46.desc: This is a custom-designed balisong, commonly known as a butterfly knife. The defining characteristic of this weapon is the fan-like opening of a freely pivoting blade, allowing rapid deployment or concealment. As a result, butterfly knives are outlawed in many countries.

47.name: Shadow Daggers
47.desc: Designed for efficient brutality, using a push dagger is as simple as throwing a punch or two.

48.name: Paracord Knife
48.desc: This fixed-blade survival knife is designed to withstand being used as both a weapon and a tool, such as for setting traps, hunting animals or cutting foliage. The handle is wrapped in a length of multi-purpose paracord.

49.name: Survival Knife
49.desc: This multi-purpose tactical knife features a serrated edge for ripping through coarse material like bone or fiber, plus a sharp gutting hook. The composite material handle is bolted to the blade with hex nuts.

50.name: Ursus Knife
50.desc: This tanto-style survival knife features a faceted blade and full tang, complete with impact pommel. No fuss, no moving parts - just a reliable blade that's ready to work.

51.name: Navaja Knife
51.desc: This marble-enamel-handled flip knife conceals a small but viciously tapered blade.

52.name: Nomad Knife
52.desc: This ergonomic tactical hunting lock-blade knife features composite handle inserts and a broad, sturdy blade, useful for cutting and prying apart material.

53.name: Stiletto Knife
53.desc: Historically a focal point of contention and even regulation, this Italian-style stiletto switchblade knife features a spring-loaded blade that can be deployed almost instantly with the push of a release catch.

54.name: Talon Knife
54.desc: This ivory-handled karambit features brass rivets and saw-tooth ridges, so it cuts on the way in, and tears on the way out.

55.name: Skeleton Knife
55.desc: This skeletonized-tang knife has been taped at the handle for improved grip. The hole allows a finger to be threaded through for stability and safety.

57.desc: These fingerless gloves have been decorated with metal studs and the Operation Bloodhound logo.

59.name: Default CT Gloves
59.desc: General-purpose tactical combat gloves designed for military or security personnel.

60.name: Sport Gloves
60.desc: Synthetic fabrics make these athletic gloves durable and eye-catching.

61.name: Driver Gloves
61.desc: These driving gloves offer protection from the elements while still maintaining tactile sensation.

62.name: Hand Wraps
62.desc: Preferred by hand-to-hand fighters, these wraps protect the knuckles and stabilize the wrist when punching.

63.name: Moto Gloves
63.desc: These bulky hard knuckled gloves can protect the wearers hands from road rash at 60 mph.

64.name: Specialist Gloves
64.desc: Durable, breathable, and stylish; these gloves are designed to take (and give) a beating.

65.name: Hydra Gloves
65.desc: These fingerless gloves have been decorated with metal studs and the Operation Hydra logo.

1779.name: Music Kit | Valve, Counter-Strike 2
1779.desc: The official music kit of Counter-Strike 2.

1780.name: Music Kit | Daniel Sadowski, Crimson Assault
1780.desc: Video Game Composer Daniel Sadowski delivers Edgy Action mixed with CRAZY FAT beats in this pulsating, exhilarating Music Pack.

1781.name: Music Kit | Noisia, Sharpened
1781.desc: Dutch Electronic Trio Noisia brings a tough, cinematic feel with a unique blend of tradition and progression.

1782.name: Music Kit | Robert Allaire, Insurgency
1782.desc: Music to crush your enemies see them driven before you from award winning composer Robert Allaire.

1783.name: Music Kit | Sean Murray, A*D*8
1783.desc: From the composer of two of the world's biggest war games, comes a sonic loadout that will bring your enemies to Hell's Gate!!

1784.name: Music Kit | Feed Me, High Noon
1784.desc: Renowned elecronic musician Feed Me, brings a western corral showdown into a modern electronic space.

1785.name: Music Kit | Dren, Death's Head Demolition
1785.desc: From game music composer Dren, this cinematic, superhero-metal inspired music pack puts the 'ill' into KILL!

1786.name: Music Kit | Austin Wintory, Desert Fire
1786.desc: Grammy nominated game composer Austin Wintory asks, why bother hunting your enemies when you can lure them in with a deadly, admittedly insane, tango?

1787.name: Music Kit | Sasha, LNOE
1787.desc: Immerse yourself in this cinematic soundtrack full of soaring strings, pulsating melodies and driving drums from the world renowned DJ / Producer Sasha

1788.name: Music Kit | Skog, Metal
1788.desc: A lesson in aggression from Metal producer, Skog.

1789.name: Music Kit | Midnight Riders, All I Want for Christmas

1790.name: Music Kit | Matt Lange, IsoRhythm
1790.desc: Indulge your aural senses in a collection of cinematic, glitchy atmospheres and hard-hitting throbbing rhythms by electronic producer and innovator Matt Lange.

1791.name: Music Kit | Mateo Messina, For No Mankind
1791.desc: Own your enemies. Pure intensity by Grammy winning composer, Mateo Messina.

1792.name: Music Kit | Various Artists, Hotline Miami
1792.desc: A multitude of electronic artists deliver brutal beats in this exhilarating Music Pack from the iconic Hotline Miami.

1793.name: Music Kit | Daniel Sadowski, Total Domination
1793.desc: Composer Daniel Sadowski raises the bar with aggressive electronic beats, creative sound fx and an exhilerating, driving, futuristic vibe. "Warning: Will cause a rise in adrenaline!"

1794.name: Music Kit | Damjan Mravunac, The Talos Principle
1794.desc: Composer Damjan Mravunac blends energetic cinematic grooves with epic choirs in this music pack featuring music from Croteam's critically acclaimed title "The Talos Principle".

1795.name: Music Kit | Proxy, Battlepack
1795.desc: Russian Heavy Electronica Artist PROXY brings his own Unique heavy artillery to Counter Strike. Hybrid audio Weaponry fused with the finest studio technology makes this pack unique.

1796.name: Music Kit | Ki:Theory, MOLOTOV
1796.desc: Recording artist and DOTA TI4 performer, Ki:Theory drops BOMBS with this searing set of razor edge dark electronic rock.

1797.name: Music Kit | Troels Folmann, Uber Blasto Phone
1797.desc: Triumphant Blastophones combine with contemporary Uberpulse in this explosive collection by ultra award winning composer Troels Folmann.

1798.name: Music Kit | Kelly Bailey, Hazardous Environments
1798.desc: Kelly Bailey, composer of Valve's Half-Life series, creates an arsenal of apocalyptic new music inspired by the darker side of the Half-Life universe.

1799.name: Music Kit | Skog, II-Headshot
1799.desc: Metal composer and producer Jocke Skog returns with an all new, hard hitting metal kit, turning the rest of the CS:GO Music Kits into something cute, warm and fuzzy. Now go become MVP so everyone can hear your awesomeness!

1800.name: Music Kit | Daniel Sadowski, The 8-Bit Kit
1800.desc: Daniel Sadowski creates the first ever 8-bit Music Kit for Counter-Strike complete with authentic 8-bit sounds.

1801.name: Music Kit | AWOLNATION, I Am
1801.desc: AWOLNATION Alternative Rocker AWOLNATION brings you a music kit for the ages. This kit is jam-packed with an eclectic selection of tunes and includes cuts from singles 'I Am' and multi-platinum hit 'Sail'.

1802.name: Music Kit | Mord Fustang, Diamonds
1802.desc: Diamonds. They are forever. Dive into the arpeggiotron of Mord Fustang with this fresh set of grooves and atmospheres.

1803.name: Music Kit | Michael Bross, Invasion!
1803.desc: Michael Bross conjures epic / cinematic techno-grunge to make you feel like a true badass in battle.

1804.name: Music Kit | Ian Hultquist, Lion's Mouth
1804.desc: Mixing pulsating strings and synths with pounding war drums, prepare yourself for battle with this thunderous soundtrack from composer Ian Hultquist.

1805.name: Music Kit | New Beat Fund, Sponge Fingerz
1805.desc: Sunny surf rock with elements of hip-hop, punk and garage pop. Keep it real and get headshots.

1806.name: Music Kit | Beartooth, Disgusting
1806.desc: Beartooth brings an agressive back-to-basics hardcore stomp that gets crowds moving and breaking stuff. A perfect soundtrack for your no-scope scout frags. Rock 'till you're dead.

1807.name: Music Kit | Lennie Moore, Java Havana Funkaloo
1807.desc: Game Composer Lennie Moore serves an aromatic, spicy blend of Jazzy Funk. Delicious when served cold, like the corpses of your enemies after you're done with them.

1808.name: Music Kit | Darude, Moments CSGO
1808.desc: Yield freely in the soundscapes of Finnish producer Darude's familiar musical flavours and tones. Enriching yourself with access to a heavy fusion of progressive overtones and scores of tingling melodic structure from the sounds banks of one of dance music's most renowned pioneers.

1809.name: Music Kit | The Verkkars, EZ4ENCE
1809.desc: The Verkkars rise through the Finnish charts with a heart-pounding tribute to ENCE. Can it really be so EZ?

1810.name: Music Kit | Halo, The Master Chief Collection
1810.desc: Give your Counter Strike auditory experience a legendary makeover with the Master Chief Collection Music Pack, featuring iconic musical moments from the Halo universe. © 2019 343 Industries. All rights reserved. Used with permission from 343 Industries. Halo: The Master Chief Collection and the Halo logo are trademarks of the Microsoft group of companies.

1811.name: Music Kit | Scarlxrd: King, Scar
1811.desc: Scarlxrd blends heavy trap beats with a flow and delivery that creates his own unique subgenre. With this exciting blend his live shows capture the attention of everyone in the crowd.

1812.name: Music Kit | Half-Life: Alyx, Anti-Citizen
1812.desc: This music kit commemorates Half-Life: Alyx, Valve's VR return to the Half-Life series. You are humanity's only chance for survival, and your immersive environmental interactions continue in Counter-Strike: Global Offensive.

1813.name: Music Kit | Amon Tobin, All for Dust
1813.desc: Legendary producer Amon Tobin lends his unique aesthetic to CS:GO. This time through tube amplifiers.

1814.name: Music Kit | Darren Korb, Hades Music Kit
1814.desc: Sure, you might miss a shot from time to time, but what never misses is this blood-pumping Music Kit straight from the Underworld of Hades, Supergiant's rogue-like dungeon crawler.

1815.name: Music Kit | Neck Deep, The Lowlife Pack
1815.desc: Prove you are not a normie (and better than everyone else on the map) with Neck Deep's new music kit, which includes songs from the band's album All Distortions Are Intentional.

1816.name: Music Kit | Scarlxrd, CHAIN$AW.LXADXUT.
1816.desc: CHAIN$AW BRINGS SCARLXRD AT HIS UNPRECENDENTED BEST WITH A RAW FLOW AND A HEAVY TRACK TO MATCH.

1817.name: Music Kit | bbno$, u mad!
1817.desc: bbno$ formulates 'the' toxic gamer anthem, u mad! Are u mad? LOL get good scrub. Research shows if you play with this Music Kit equipped you'll immediately go from Silver to Global.

1818.name: Music Kit | The Verkkars & n0thing, Flashbang Dance
1818.desc: From sunny California to frigid Lapland, Counter-Strike legend n0thing and The Verkkars combine powers to create the smash hit, Flashbang Dance! 3, 2, 1 you’re blind!

1819.name: Music Kit | Perfect World, 花脸 Hua Lian (Painted Face)
1819.desc: Celebrate the 5th anniversary of CS:GO's release in China with a one of a kind music kit, 花脸 Hua Lian (Painted Face). This kit combines folk Qinqiang opera (the earliest Chinese style Rock 'n' Roll) and modern Rock 'n' Roll. Whether you are engulfed in smoke or blinded by a flashbang, don't get lost!

1820.name: Music Kit | Denzel Curry, ULTIMATE
1820.desc: Denzel brings his signature energy to CS:GO as he traverses trap, jazz, and drum and bass beats. This kit features Denzel's hits "Walkin", "ULTIMATE", and more, so break out the nickel-plated chrome Berettas and crank up the intensity with the ULTIMATE music kit.

1821.name: Music Kit | Beartooth, Aggressive
1821.desc: Beartooth is back for round two. This new music kit hits harder and is even more aggressive. We've also made the MVP anthem extra heavy so your opponents feel really bad after they've lost to you.

1822.name: Music Kit | Blitz Kids, The Good Youth
1822.desc: British Pop/Punk band Blitz Kids brings you the perfect music kit for rushing B while thinking about those night drives you had with your friends in High School. This kit is for going fast and feeling young.

1823.name: Music Kit | Hundredth, FREE
1823.desc: Hundredth is bringing heavy to the world with their unique take on melodic hardcore. Break free or return to Dust with this perfect soundtrack for fragging the unworthy.

1824.name: Music Kit | Neck Deep, Life's Not Out To Get You
1824.desc: Sometimes you just need some Pop Punk to get you through the day. Whether it is dealing with campers or losing a massive kill streak, Neck Deep is here to prove that Life's Not Out To Get You, but the other team still is.

1825.name: Music Kit | Roam, Backbone
1825.desc: Roam delivers fast, straight-forward Pop Punk that gets crowd and players alike moving. Prove you have a Backbone with this perfect soundtrack for rushing in and obliterating the other team before they even realize they're deadweight.

1826.name: Music Kit | Twin Atlantic, GLA
1826.desc: Heavier, rowdier, and louder than ever, Twin Atlantic comes to CS:GO ready to help you melt the faces with the firepower of Scottish rock.

1827.name: Music Kit | Skog, III-Arena
1827.desc: Skog is back with a third crushing metal kit. This time with an electro-organic twist to the music, combining massive guitar riffs with equally massive drops, loop elements and drones.

1828.name: Music Kit | Austin Wintory, Bachram
1828.desc: Austin Wintory mixes Celtic fantasy with sizzling electronics and a generous helping of Peter Hollens' vocals in this genre-bending Music Kit.

1829.name: Music Kit | Dren, Gunman Taco Truck
1829.desc: The apocalyptic mariachi soundtrack from the indie game hit, Gunman Taco Truck, comes to CS:GO with intense Mexican flavored tunes like Pollo Diablo and Persecución de Helltain!

1830.name: Music Kit | Daniel Sadowski, Eye of the Dragon
1830.desc: From the composer who brought you "Total Domination", "The 8-Bit Kit" and "Crimson Assault", comes "Eye Of The Dragon". Music composer Daniel Sadowski mixes Ninjas + Guns + Hip-Hop + Techno to create an action-packed Music Kit. Ninjas are known for their fast and precise attacks, yet they can be invisible to their enemy.

1831.name: Music Kit | Tree Adams and Ben Bromfield, M.U.D.D. FORCE
1831.desc: Alchemists of a powerful chaos that is M.U.D.D. FORCE - composers Tree Adams and Ben Bromfield weld epic battle motifs and grinding synths into a Maelstrom of full throttle destruction.

1832.name: Music Kit | Tim Huling, Neo Noir
1832.desc: Composer Tim Huling delivers classic film-noir style tracks blended with contemporary grooves and beats.

1833.name: Music Kit | Sam Marshall, Bodacious
1833.desc: Inspired by the funky video game music of the early 90s, composer Sam Marshall cooks up some classic game nostalgia with a spicy modern sauce.

1834.name: Music Kit | Matt Levine, Drifter
1834.desc: Composer Matt Levine delivers raw swagger in this gritty homage to the Spaghetti Western. It has never felt better to say, "go ahead, make my day..."

1835.name: Music Kit | Austin Wintory, Mocha Petal
1835.desc: Austin Wintory answers the question humanity has asked for ages: what happens if you merge beer garden accordion polka music with grungy heavy metal?

1836.name: Music Kit | Chipzel, ~Yellow Magic~
1836.desc: Video game composer and chiptune legend Chipzel brings a glitchy Speak & Spell inspired mashup of hybrid styles packed with fun, funk and flavour.

1837.name: Music Kit | Freaky DNA, Vici
1837.desc: Opera. 8-bit sounds. Analogue synths. What's not to love? Chiptune specialist Freaky DNA and soprano Leanne Koch team up for some heavy beats and good times!

1838.name: Music Kit | Jesse Harlin, Astro Bellum
1838.desc: Composer Jesse Harlin delivers bombastic space opera drama inspired by classic sci-fi of the 70s, 80s, and beyond.

1839.name: Music Kit | Laura Shigihara: Work Hard, Play Hard
1839.desc: Video game composer and developer Laura Shigihara will help you tell everyone loudly and proudly that you're the MVP. Have fun with this unique blend of 90s dance, retro video game synth, and just a hint of Plants vs. Zombies.

1840.name: Music Kit | Sarah Schachner, KOLIBRI
1840.desc: Brought to you by Sarah Schachner, a dystopian goth choir of self-aware, Scandinavian robots decide that humanity must be eliminated.

1841.name: Music Kit | 3kliksphilip, Heading for the Source
1841.desc: On a quest to go pro, or unintentionally going low? Let this kit’s 80’s synths and dreamy melodies take you back. Back, back, back... to the good old days.

1842.name: Music Kit | Humanity's Last Breath, Void
1842.desc: Swedish Band Humanity's Last Breath drops in heavy with their Void Music Kit. Pounding drums, colossal riffs and an atmosphere to send shivers up your spine.

1843.name: Music Kit | Juelz, Shooters
1843.desc: Neo trap synths, gritty 808s, an epic piano riff, and a plethora of gunfire sound effects. The OG trap anthem "Shooters" by Juelz makes for a truly elite Music Kit. Suitable for MVPs only.

1844.name: Music Kit | Knock2, dashstar*
1844.desc: dashstar*, the iconic bass house anthem from Knock2, provides non-stop energy that captures the young San Diego native’s mantra, "no limit".

1845.name: Music Kit | Meechy Darko, Gothic Luxury
1845.desc: Grab a Glock and equip this music kit to be transported to the center of New York's underground hip-hop scene.

1846.name: Music Kit | Sullivan King, Lock Me Up
1846.desc: Love the chase? Love the hunt? Hard rock, metal, and dubstep collide in Sullivan King's soundtrack for becoming unstoppable.

8605.name: Patch | Sunset Wave
8605.desc: A new day on the ocean...

8620.name: Agent | Ground Rebel  | Elite Crew
8620.desc:
An expert in local knowledge for Elite Crew's urban operations, Ground Rebels are known for keeping an ear to the ground.

That's the signal.

8621.name: Agent | Osiris | Elite Crew
8621.desc:
Osiris earned his nickname from passing judgement, often too quickly, on his marks. His reasoning is simple: "When your time is as valuable as mine, why make small talk?" 

Confident, skilled, and quick to act, Osiris takes pleasure in dispatching targets with unrivaled efficiency.

Any objections?

8622.name: Agent | Prof. Shahmat | Elite Crew
8622.desc:
After graduating Magna Cum Laude, Prof. Shahmat began teaching to impart knowledge. With every class Shahmat realized his pupils didn't have the same revolutionary desires that he did. 

Recognizing that his mind was beginning to dull, he decided to seek a new challenge—mastering the art of war.

Watch and learn.

8623.name: Agent | The Elite Mr. Muhlik | Elite Crew
8623.desc:
First appeared operating as an 'Acquisitions Consultant' for arms industry magnates, Mr. Muhlik quickly worked his way on to many Most Wanted lists worldwide. Unconfirmed reports suggest he is the last surviving heir to a recently-deposed Middle Eastern monarch. 

With evidence of elite military training, international private education, and numerous international bank accounts, it's suspected Mr. Muhlik is maneuvering to rebuild sovereign power over his family's historical lands.

Pressure and time.

8624.name: Agent | Jungle Rebel | Elite Crew
8624.desc:
Elite Crew's wetland and jungle based ground rebel. Deadly in the shade(s).

It's dark and I'm wearing sunglasses.

8625.name: Agent | Soldier | Phoenix
8625.desc:
A capable shooter recruited by Phoenix to assist with Territory Reclamation Campaigns. Soldiers are extremely deadly alone, and even more so in numbers.

When do we shoot?

8626.name: Agent | Enforcer | Phoenix
8626.desc:
A multidisciplinary contract hitman for the Phoenix Connexion. Enforcers don't take all assignments, just the ones they find interesting.

Time is money.

8627.name: Agent | Slingshot | Phoenix
8627.desc:
Slingshot is a critical component of Phoenix Connexion's dominance in close-range combat.

Tightly wound and capable of devastating results with little resources, Slingshot earned his nickname after retaking the Phoenix compound with only an M9 Bayonet and recovered weapons.

If I can knife, I knife.

8628.name: Agent | Street Soldier | Phoenix
8628.desc:
A Phoenix ground force gang with expertise in high density urban environments. Their knowledge of back roads and alleyways are only surpassed by local taxi drivers, which are rumored to make up a significant portion of their numbers.

I know a shortcut.

8629.name: Agent | Operator | FBI SWAT
8629.desc:
Members of the FBI's SWAT team are deployed in high-risk situations. Counterterrorism, hostage rescue, and bomb defusals are a few of the many disciplines FBI SWAT agents specialize in.

Fidelity, Bravery, Integrity.

8630.name: Agent | Markus Delrow | FBI HRT
8630.desc:
There's no detail too small for Markus Delrow. Equipment, battle plans, oppositional tactics—you name it—and he's already thought of it twice. 

Being two steps ahead is what he does best, and Delrow takes pride in being the brains of the operation.

All that's left is to execute.

8631.name: Agent | Michael Syfers  | FBI Sniper
8631.desc:
An ex-Division I athlete, Syfers was recruited by the FBI after a catastrophic knee injury ended his sports career early. Yet even in adversity he remained positive. 

It's rare to find someone whose desire to succeed is matched by their desire to do good, but Syfers checks both boxes.

Naturally, I finished my reps.

8632.name: Agent | Special Agent Ava | FBI
8632.desc:
Initially underestimated, Special Agent Ava soon became her team's ultimate secret weapon. 

Despite receiving three out of five possible FBI Honorary Medals, Ava is surprisingly indifferent to her accomplishments. The way she sees it, it's nothing compared to growing up with four older brothers in urban New Jersey. 

Special Agent Ava takes pleasure from the simple things: clean wins, cold beer, and turning bad guys into thin crust pizza pie.

They see me. They're confused. And then they're dead.

8633.name: Agent | 'Blueberries' Buckshot | NSWC SEAL
8633.desc:
Known as SEAL Team's "Weapons Sommelier" Buckshot has thoroughly field-tested and reviewed almost every available military weapon in staggering depth. ST6 relies on Buckshot's knowledge of lesser-known guns for edge case advantages in ground based operations.

Seen here sporting the classic NUE Type 1 uniform otherwise known as 'blueberries'.

They talk to me. The guns. They have feelings.

8634.name: Agent | 'Two Times' McCoy | TACP Cavalry
8634.desc:
'Two Times' McCoy earned his nickname by completing TACP's field training twice. Official records mark this up to a scheduling mix-up, but his teammates report restraining him from completing the trifecta.

With inhuman reserves of physical and mental stamina, McCoy often finds himself the last person standing at the end of any conflict—physical and verbal alike.

His yellow scarf is a tribute to his time with 1st Cavalry Division.

Yep. Still here.

8635.name: Agent | 3rd Commando Company | KSK
8635.desc:
An elite soldier from Germany's Kommando Spezialkräfte, members of 3rd Commando Company are hand-picked to be part of KSK's Operational Forces.

This is not relevant to the task at hand.

8636.name: Agent | Seal Team 6 Soldier | NSWC SEAL
8636.desc:
Combat-ready and hungry for wins, SEAL Team 6 soldiers know how to get the job done.

I'm just happy to be here.

8637.name: Agent | Buckshot | NSWC SEAL
8637.desc:
Known as SEAL Team's "Weapons Sommelier" Buckshot has thoroughly field-tested and reviewed almost every available military weapon in staggering depth. ST6 relies on Buckshot's knowledge of lesser-known guns for edge case advantages in ground based operations—but in the interest of time, they strenuously avoid casual conversation on the topic.

They talk to me. The guns. They have feelings.

8638.name: Agent | 'Two Times' McCoy | USAF TACP
8638.desc:
'Two Times' McCoy earned his nickname by completing TACP's field training twice. Official records mark this up to a scheduling mix-up, but his teammates report restraining him from completing the trifecta.

With inhuman reserves of physical and mental stamina, McCoy often finds himself the last person standing at the end of any conflict—physical and verbal alike.

Yep. Still here.

8639.name: Agent | Lt. Commander Ricksaw | NSWC SEAL
8639.desc:
Lt. Commander Ricksaw's comically laissez-faire attitude toward heavy combat keeps his SEAL team calm and deadly in the most dire situations. 

Having lead more special ops than any other SEAL to date, Ricksaw knows life is short, and encourages his team to make the most of the time they have—including cheerfully serving up bullets and frag grenades to high- value targets at any and all occasions.

Hotdogs, hellcats and hand grenades. Hooya!

8640.name: Agent | Primeiro Tenente | Brazilian 1st Battalion
8640.desc:
As a combat survival specialist in deep jungle operations, the Brazilian 1st Battalion sharpen their teeth alongside the banks of the mighty Amazon River.

Surprises welcome.

8641.name: Agent | Rezan the Redshirt | Sabre
8641.desc:
An expert grenadier and the once-celebrated author of The Joy of Preparedness, Rezan the Redshirt is Sabre's self-appointed Head of Operations.

Over time, Rezan has learned to control his fiery temper—now he wears his explosive rage on his sleeves.

I take great pride in my work.

8642.name: Agent | Dragomir | Sabre
8642.desc: A man of few words, Dragomir is disturbingly patient. Known for holding position for days at a time, some say he's one of Sabre's best marksman. Others say he's napping. No one really knows. No one left alive, anyway....I wait.

8643.name: Agent | Maximus | Sabre
8643.desc:
Motivated by a simmering inner rage and a lifelong obsession with vengeance for transgressions large, small, and seemingly insignificant, Maximus is Sabre's first choice for close quarter mission support. No grudge is too small to be repaid in blood.

No, YOU overreacted.

8644.name: Agent | Rezan The Ready | Sabre
8644.desc:
An expert grenadier and the once-celebrated author of The Joy of Preparedness, Rezan The Ready is Sabre's self-appointed Head of Operations.

His fiery temper when things get out of hand has earned him the alternative nickname Rezan the Red—but never to his face.

I take great pride in my work.

8645.name: Agent | Blackwolf | Sabre
8645.desc:
Blackwolf stalks Sabre's enemies with preternatural determination and focus. Raised deep within the bitter forests of Eastern Europe, he can sense human presence with exceptional accuracy—and he knows what to do when he's sensed it.

I don't need to see them to kill them.

8646.name: Agent | 'The Doctor' Romanov | Sabre
8646.desc:
After expertly smuggling pharmaceuticals across disputed borders for over 30 years, the 'doctor' now leads Sabre's Utility Disruption Operations. Rumoured to be responsible for the synchronized destruction of several UN power facilities, Romanov is known by his enemies to be calculating, deliberate, and frighteningly precise. Of course, his mother says he's just mixed up with the wrong crowd.

It's simple. We make a plan and the plan is to win.

8647.name: Agent | Dragomir | Sabre Footsoldier
8647.desc: Sabre has noticed that enemies seem to die quite frequently around Dragomir, even though they've never actually seen him shoot his gun. They're happy to keep him around... for now....I wait.

8648.name: Agent | B Squadron Officer | SAS
8648.desc:
Highly classified and incredibly lethal, Officers in the SAS spend years sharpening their skills through infiltration, hostage rescue, and —REDACTED— missions not fit for the public eye.

Who dares, wins.

8649.name: Agent | D Squadron Officer | NZSAS
8649.desc:
Highly classified and incredibly lethal, Officers in the SAS spend years sharpening their skills through infiltration, hostage rescue, and —REDACTED— missions not fit for the public eye.

Who dares, wins.

8650.name: Agent | Cmdr. Mae 'Dead Cold' Jamison | SWAT
8650.desc:
Cmdr. 'Dead Cold' Jamison has just about seen it all. Skeptical and wry in the midst of deadly combat, others could mistake her for being nonchalant about the chaos at hand. They would be wrong. Nothing gets past Dead Cold, not bad guys with AK-47s, junior officers that call her 'Ma'am,' or an opportunity to make elite officers smirk under pressure.

You're gonna find out.

8651.name: Agent | 1st Lieutenant Farlow | SWAT
8651.desc:
Smart as a whip and relentlessly polite, 1st Lieutenant Farlow is one of the most beloved and respected officers in SWAT. A master tactician in hostage and barricade situations, Farlow quickly climbed the SWAT ranks. Don't be fooled by her overwhelmingly cheerful nature--she can dispatch bad guys in the blink of an eye and not think twice about it.

What are they doing over there? Drinking milkshakes?

8652.name: Agent | John 'Van Healen' Kask | SWAT
8652.desc:
John 'Van Healen' Kask is one of SWATs best tactical defence units and on-site military paramedics. He also shreds a mean guitar—sometimes mid-operation. He says it helps get his teammates' blood pumping just as effectively as an AED, which he keeps ready in case of emergency.

I can bring you back to life, but I can't make you live.

8653.name: Agent | Bio-Haz Specialist | SWAT
8653.desc:
The SWAT's Biological Hazard Specialists are trained to handle worst case bio warfare situations. Terrorists planning to unleash a bio hazard attack upon unsuspecting civilians do not want to deal with these guys.

Tacita Sed Mortiferum.

8654.name: Agent | Sergeant Bombson | SWAT
8654.desc:
Tyler Bobson earned his moniker after becoming SWAT's go-to officer for efficient Explosive Ordnance Disposal. With his uncanny ability to locate even the most well hidden IEDs, Bombson's keen hearing is outclassed only by the noble Greater Wax Moth.

Yeah, I heard that.

8655.name: Agent | Chem-Haz Specialist | SWAT
8655.desc:
The SWAT Chemical Hazard Specialists are able to survive and succeed in toxic environment operations for hours at a time. Where others run away, they run in.

Feels like home.

8656.name: Agent | Lieutenant 'Tree Hugger' Farlow | SWAT
8656.desc:
No one else knows how to enjoy combat ops that require sunscreen, mosquito repellant and M4A4 assault rifles quite like Farlow does.

Kinda nice to get out of the cold don't ya think?

8657.name: Agent | Bloody Darryl The Strapped | The Professionals
8657.desc:
Before he was leader of the heist gang 'The Professionals' Sir Bloody Darryl was more simply called, Bloody Darryl. Still your friendly neighborhood psychopath in every sense of the word. Not actually Australian according to Australians.

I'm just gonna give them a bit of Razzle Dazzle.

8658.name: Agent | Sir Bloody Miami Darryl | The Professionals
8658.desc:
The leader of 'The Professionals' can be described as cocky, wisecracking, and scarily indifferent with regards to the suffering of others. He would say he's just a bloke—a bloke that likes to have a bit of fun on the weekend with the local armed tax collectors. He downplays the severity of any heavy situations that come his way, even if he's the last man standing, riddled with bullets, with only seconds left to blow the safe.

This white hockey mask and floral shirt were popular choices during his Vice phase.

Got my hair combed back and my sunglasses on.

8659.name: Agent | Safecracker Voltzmann | The Professionals
8659.desc:
Weird, quirky, unhinged; a few words that describe The Professionals' safecracker and technical mastermind. When she is not mumbling to herself about the flawed assumptions inherent within the profit maximization paradox, Safecracker serves as a morally questionable but highly efficient 'fundraising expert.' She enjoys short walks on pavement, the sound of cable ties being fastened, and testing explosive prototypes under immense pressure.

Don't blow it. DO blow the bomb though, okay? We do want that.

8660.name: Agent | Little Kev | The Professionals
8660.desc:
The Professional who makes heavy weapons look weightless, Little Kev is the soft spoken 'little' brother of Sir Bloody Darryl. His older brother's bodyguard since age 5, Little Kev developed a knack for quelling 'people problems' before they arise. Sir Darryl assigned him Human Resources Manager for the entire Professionals organization.

We're getting this done either way.

8661.name: Agent | Getaway Sally | The Professionals
8661.desc:
Small enough to hide in plain sight but loud enough to frighten the biggest enemies, Getaway Sally is The Professionals' first pick for tight quarter Wealth Acquisition Projects.  A talented weaver of controlled chaos, Getaway Sally has the improvisational skills to turn the tables on any dire heist and hostage situations.

Now you don't see me, and now you still don't.

8662.name: Agent | Number K | The Professionals
8662.desc:
In his 'Wealth Acquisition Specialist' application form, Number K wrote the letter 'K' in every number field, but his talent with handguns made him more than qualified for the position. Number K keeps the details of his life private—none of his colleagues have seen his face—making him one of The Professionals' most feared heist managers.

Don't count us down. Just say go.

8663.name: Agent | Sir Bloody Silent Darryl | The Professionals
8663.desc:
The leader of 'The Professionals' can be described as cocky, wisecracking, and scarily indifferent with regards to the suffering of others. He would say he's just a bloke—a bloke that likes to have a bit of fun on the weekend with the local armed tax collectors. He downplays the severity of any heavy situations that come his way, even if he's the last man standing, riddled with bullets, with only seconds left to blow the safe.

This 'Vow of Silence' mask was Darryl's response to organizational complaints about his logorrhea....

8664.name: Agent | Sir Bloody Skullhead Darryl | The Professionals
8664.desc:
The leader of 'The Professionals' can be described as cocky, wisecracking, and scarily indifferent with regards to the suffering of others. He would say he's just a bloke—a bloke that likes to have a bit of fun on the weekend with the local armed tax collectors. He downplays the severity of any heavy situations that come his way, even if he's the last man standing, riddled with bullets, with only seconds left to blow the safe.

This black mask has been painted with a white skull, a useful bit of intimidation back when The Professionals were just getting started.

Are we gonna bloody finish this thing or what?!

8665.name: Agent | Sir Bloody Darryl Royale | The Professionals
8665.desc:
The leader of 'The Professionals' can be described as cocky, wisecracking, and scarily indifferent with regards to the suffering of others. He would say he's just a bloke—a bloke that likes to have a bit of fun on the weekend with the local armed tax collectors. He downplays the severity of any heavy situations that come his way, even if he's the last man standing, riddled with bullets, with only seconds left to blow the safe.

This gold mask with a crown stencil commemorates The Professionals' first visit to Monaco.

Do you know what they call a cheeseburger in Monaco?

8666.name: Agent | Sir Bloody Loudmouth Darryl | The Professionals
8666.desc:
The leader of 'The Professionals' can be described as cocky, wisecracking, and scarily indifferent with regards to the suffering of others. He would say he's just a bloke—a bloke that likes to have a bit of fun on the weekend with the local armed tax collectors. He downplays the severity of any heavy situations that come his way, even if he's the last man standing, riddled with bullets, with only seconds left to blow the safe.

This mask has been painted with clown makeup, perfect for taking candy from rich spoiled babies....The crying on the inside kind, I guess.

8667.name: Agent | Sous-Lieutenant Medic | Gendarmerie Nationale
8667.desc:
Medics of the Gendarmerie National have a well-deserved reputation for providing life saving interventions using anything at their disposal. From improvised AEDs to jungle medicine to precise covering fire, the medics of the Gendarm have your back—no matter what.

It is better to prevent than to heal.

8668.name: Agent | Chem-Haz Capitaine | Gendarmerie Nationale
8668.desc:
As leader for Chemical and BioHazard combat operations in populated areas, the Gendarmerie Chem-Haz Capitaine plays a crucial role within the organization. Celebrated for orchestrating the successful rescue of an entire domestic airport's civilian occupancy in the infamous sarin gas attack of 1997, the Chem-Haz Capitaine is the epitome of preparedness and composure.

Don't forget to breathe.

8669.name: Agent | Chef d'Escadron Rouchard | Gendarmerie Nationale
8669.desc:
Born into an old aristocratic family, Rouchard enlisted in the Gendarmerie Nationale at her first opportunity as a way to avoid compulsory enrollment at a notorious Swiss finishing school for young women. As Aspirant in the Gendarmerie, Rouchard quickly impressed her senior ranks by excelling in offensive strategy and hostage negotiations, but most of all, blade-based combat. Several promotions later she is best known by her moniker 'Le Couteau' (The Knife), although some would say this is because she can be a bit blunt at times. Today, Rouchard gets called in when no one else knows what to do.

It is but a scratch.

8670.name: Agent | Aspirant | Gendarmerie Nationale
8670.desc:
Aspirants of the Gendarmerie are highly trained military police cadets responsible for assisting in rural combat operations. To say most are eager for action in the field is an understatement.

C'est la vie.

8671.name: Agent | Officer Jacques Beltram | Gendarmerie Nationale
8671.desc:
A highly decorated Officer for the Gendarmerie, Beltram was awarded the Legion of Honor for swapping places with a hostage and thwarting terrorist activity on more than one occasion. Beltram is a hero, a single father, and a passionate consumer of pain au chocolate at all times of day.

We do what we have to do.

8672.name: Agent | Cmdr. Davida 'Goggles' Fernandez | SEAL Frogman
8672.desc:
Possessing an exquisite mammalian dive reflex, Cmdr. Fernandez is able to slow her heart rate to undetectable levels and navigate darkness, ice, and deep sea defense systems. She excels in her human aquatic potential and her skill as an elite marksman and soldier. 'Goggles' earned her nickname when a bullet struck her left eye—or would have—if it weren't for 'Wet Sox' reminding her to grab her full kit 'for the last time!' Despite her occasional forgetfulness, Cmdr. Fernandez is one of two elite combat diver SEALs to be awarded The Navy Cross for classified underwater operations.

Be still my beating heart.

8673.name: Agent | Cmdr. Frank 'Wet Sox' Baroud | SEAL Frogman
8673.desc:
First on deck and last off it, Cmdr. Frank Baroud is a third generation SEAL and second combat diver ever to receive The Navy Cross medal; 'Goggles' was the first. Count on Baroud to solve the most complicated underwater and ground based conflict situations, like the time he defused several IED's which were planted in a network of flooded caves beneath a US embassy. Baroud chalks it up to his impeccable attention to detail, because after all, when your life depends on the equipment you're wearing, a simple mistake may be the last one you make. His uncompromising attention to detail earned him the nickname 'Wet Sox'.

Double check it. Then triple check it. Then check it again.

8674.name: Agent | Lieutenant Rex Krikey | SEAL Frogman
8674.desc:
Lieutenant Krikey is a prime choice for all jungle and wetlands combat operations. His expertise in handling wild reptiles big and small has saved both him and his fellow frogmen on more than one occasion.

I'm just an apex predator that enjoys meeting other apex predators.

8675.name: Agent | Elite Trapper Solman | Guerrilla Warfare
8675.desc:
On a hot summer day on the outskirt islands of the Caribbean, Solman, relaxing on a small yet expensive vacation tour, was taken hostage by the infamous Guerrilla Warfare (GW). Overhearing his captors talk about the division of ransom money, Solman negotiated his own release if he delivered three additional hostages within 24 hours. And deliver he did, armed with only money, charm, and a way with words reserved for the world's most horrific cult leaders. Stunned by his lack of empathy for his fellow tourists and his ability to deliver a steady supply of 'ransom units' (people) the GW negotiated a position for Solman among them. Taking the highest percentage of hostage random money of any member of the GW, Solman had won the game before it even started.

You only need three things to fix a bad situation: money, charm, and a loaded weapon.

8676.name: Agent | Crasswater The Forgotten | Guerrilla Warfare
8676.desc:
Former Navy SEAL Capt. Crasswater was taken prisoner by the Guerrilla Warfare (GW) while serving in the Middle East during the 1990's. After a botched rescue attempt by ST6 and subsequent military cover-up, the US Navy declared Crasswater deceased. Over the years of his imprisonment, his patriotism and 'no man left behind' mantra eroded into bitter hatred for all things USA. Newly armed with a severe case of Stockholm Syndrome, Crasswater joined the Trappers of the GW. After a series of 'trust building' attacks on western embassies, Crasswater became GW's most valuable asset—bringing military discipline and organization to an otherwise chaotic gang of rebel fighters. In recent years Crasswater has grown new GW cells at undisclosed locations across Central America.

Just one more forget-me-not.

8677.name: Agent | Arno The Overgrown | Guerrilla Warfare
8677.desc:
Disgraced heavyweight boxing champion, Arno The Overgrown was discovered by Guerrilla Warfare (GW) Trappers living out of a cave. Over the years Arno had become an expert survivalist and big-game hunter—able to live off the land for an indefinite amount of time carrying only his flint stick and sharpened hunting knife. Rumors of Arno eventually spread to nearby townships where he came to attention of Guerrilla Warfare (GW). Wanting to recruit Arno's flawless hunting and fighting skills, the GW failed to coax Arno from his habitat, that is, until they threatened to stop visiting him with hot fresh Milk Tarts every month.

It isn't the loneliness that kills you, it's the absence of Melk Tarts.

8678.name: Agent | Col. Mangos Dabisi | Guerrilla Warfare
8678.desc:
Early in his life Col. Mangos Dabisi was trained and promoted within Ugandan military. He ended his military career with a rare Dishonorable Discharge for intimidating his subordinates into paying him 'sleep well money'—promising a good night's sleep to those who paid him. Turns out, a good night's sleep was merely a lack of intentional injuries inflicted by Dabisi himself. Dabisi's imposing stature and military skill made him an attractive acquisition for the Guerrilla Warfare (GW). Constantly over-using force and needing to be reined in, Dabisi's reputation as a GW powerhouse is well deserved.

I chop your doller or your neck. You choose.

8679.name: Agent | Vypa Sista of the Revolution | Guerrilla Warfare
8679.desc:
A notorious rebel and brilliant improviser, Vypa is one of twelve sisters born into poverty and left to fend for themselves at the age of seven. Vypa's solo attacks against her country's military dictatorship were so prolific the military assumed her work was the result of a small team of people. At one point, Vypa mistook a remote Guerrilla Warfare (GW) training ground for a government outpost. Shortly after invoking one of her infamous 'sting and choke' maneuvers on the camp she realized her mistake, but not before she had Capt. Crasswater tied up to a tree and threatened at knife point. Impressed and a little frightened, Crasswater recruited Vypa and her sisters into the GW. Together they now lead all jungle-based GW missions and 'government awareness' campaigns.

Don't worry, it's just me.

8680.name: Agent | Trapper Aggressor | Guerrilla Warfare
8680.desc:
The experienced and cunning Trapper Aggressors utilize ruthless efficiency in capturing and securing tourists as hostages. As experts in wetland and jungle-based guerrilla tactics, any rescue missions involving Trapper Aggressors are doomed to fail.

The promise of air conditioning and iced tea. It works every time.

8681.name: Agent | 'Medium Rare' Crasswater | Guerrilla Warfare
8681.desc:
Former Navy SEAL Capt. Crasswater was taken prisoner by the Guerrilla Warfare (GW) while serving in the Middle East during the 1990's. After a botched rescue attempt by ST6 and subsequent military cover-up, the US Navy declared Crasswater deceased. Over the years of his imprisonment, his patriotism and 'no man left behind' mantra eroded into bitter hatred for all things USA. Newly armed with a severe case of Stockholm Syndrome, Crasswater joined the Trappers of the GW. After a series of 'trust building' attacks on western embassies, Crasswater became GW's most valuable asset—bringing military discipline and organization to an otherwise chaotic gang of rebel fighters. In recent years Crasswater has grown new GW cells at undisclosed locations across Central America.

Just one more forget-me-not.

8682.name: Agent | Trapper | Guerrilla Warfare
8682.desc:
Sharp, stealthy, and the bane of organised military units everywhere, the Trappers are rarely seen before they are felt.

We hunt you.

This capsule contains a single sticker autographed by one of the players from Fnatic at DreamHack Cluj-Napoca 2015.

50% of the proceeds from the sale of this capsule support the included players and organizations.

That sticker can be applied to any weapon you own and can be scraped to look more worn. You can scrape the same sticker multiple times, making it a bit more worn each time, until it is removed from the weapon.

11272.name: Kukri Knife
11272.desc: Used in traditional rituals, such as weddings or stabbings.

11273.name: Dual Berettas | Hideout
11273.desc:
It has been custom painted with a multicolored design.

Step right up, don't be shy

11274.name: Five-SeveN | Hybrid
11274.desc:
It has been custom painted with a silver base coat and bright purple stripes.

Party in the front, party in the back

11275.name: Glock-18 | Block-18
11275.desc:
It has been custom painted to section the weapon off into colored blocks.

Blocked and loaded

11276.name: AK-47 | Inheritance
11276.desc:
This custom paint job takes inspiration from traditional Chinese porcelain and Delft Blauw art.

A "family" heirloom, passed through generations

11277.name: AWP | Chrome Cannon
11277.desc:
Custom painted with mirror coat paint, this AWP is finished with multicolored accents and a carbon fiber scope.

"Where'd this come from? Why do you ask?" - Booth, Arms Dealer

11278.name: M4A4 | Etch Lord
11278.desc:
It has been custom painted to appear as if it was etched into.

It's just a phase

11279.name: MAC-10 | Light Box
11279.desc:
It has been custom painted to appear as if you are looking into the back of the MAC-10.

Custom built

11280.name: UMP-45 | Motorized
11280.desc:
This custom paint job resembles a combustion engine, repurposed to be used as a weapon.

"With routine maintenance this'll last at least 500,000 bullets!"

11281.name: XM1014 | Irezumi
11281.desc:
A snake has been custom painted atop a gold-colored base in a style inspired by the Japanese tattoo art style Irezumi.

Snakes represent wisdom and prophecy, two words which best describe XM1014 users

11282.name: Sawed-Off | Analog Input
11282.desc:
It has been custom painted with diagonal bands of color and the letters "X", "Y", "B", and "A".

19 in 99

11283.name: Tec-9 | Slag
11283.desc:
It has been custom painted to appear handmade, from the grip to the welding on the receiver.

You have insurance, right?

11284.name: MP7 | Just Smile
11284.desc:
The blue and purple base coat is finished with a smiley face and the words "Just Smile" in yellow.

"Say cheeeeese"

11285.name: Nova | Dark Sigil
11285.desc:
It has been custom painted with longships and dragons.

It emerged from the fog of war

11286.name: SSG 08 | Dezastre
11286.desc:
It has been custom painted with a high tech black, white, and red design.

Always follow manufacturer guidelines for safe use

11287.name: M4A1-S | Black Lotus
11287.desc:
It has been custom painted with a black lotus flower over a blue and purple base.

Adds 2 kills during rifle round, then is discarded

11288.name: USP-S | Jawbreaker
11288.desc:
This custom painted USP-S uses high gloss paint and depicts a dog barking from the grip to the silencer. The silencer reads "GOOD DOGGY".

I said "sit"!

11289.name: Kukri Knife | Forest DDPAT
11289.desc:
It has been painted using a Digital Disruptive Pattern (DDPAT) hydrographic.

By the time you're close enough to notice the pixels it's already too late

11290.name: Kukri Knife | Crimson Web
11290.desc:
It has been painted using a spider web-patterned hydrographic over a red base coat and finished with a semi-gloss topcoat.

Be careful where you walk, you never know where the web is spread

11291.name: Kukri Knife | Fade
11291.desc:
It has been painted by airbrushing transparent paints that fade together over a chrome base coat.

This isn't just a weapon, it's a conversation piece - Imogen, Arms Dealer In Training

11292.name: Kukri Knife | Blue Steel
11292.desc:
It has been cold blued.

This is the malbec of weapon design - Booth, Arms Dealer

11293.name: Kukri Knife | Stained
11293.desc:
It has been given a forced patina using lemon and mustard dripped onto the surface.

If you think it's messy now, wait until you see it under a blacklight

11294.name: Kukri Knife | Case Hardened
11294.desc:
It has been color case-hardened through the application of wood charcoal at high temperatures.

A little color never hurt anyone

11295.name: Kukri Knife | Slaughter
11295.desc:
It has been painted in a zebra-stripe pattern with aluminum and chrome paints with various reflectivities, and has then been covered with a tomato red candy coat.

Valeria doesn't pay Javier to ask questions... she pays him to pry out answers

11296.name: Kukri Knife | Safari Mesh
11296.desc:
It has been spray-painted using mesh fencing and cardboard cutouts as stencils.

A predator is a predator, no matter the environment

11297.name: Kukri Knife | Boreal Forest
11297.desc:
It has been painted using a forest camouflage hydrographic.

The woods can be a dangerous place... never travel alone

11298.name: Kukri Knife | Urban Masked
11298.desc:
It has been spray-painted using a tangle of masking tape as a stencil.

True power is demonstrated with subtle application

11299.name: Kukri Knife | Scorched
11299.desc:
It has been spray-painted in a sun-dappled pattern.

The Phoenix is not a symbol of destruction... it's a symbol of rebirth - Valeria Jenner, Revolutionary

11300.name: Kukri Knife | Night Stripe
11300.desc:
It has been spray-painted with a tape mask pattern in a night ops color scheme.

Spray... Pray... Paint... Stab.

11301.name: Music Kit | DRYDEN, Feel The Power
11301.desc: What else needs to be said? Feel The Power. Lock in with this high-energy electro Music Kit from DRYDEN.

11302.name: Music Kit | ISOxo, inhuman
11302.desc: Made especially for those games when you feel... different. Haunt your enemies round after round with the "inhuman" Music Kit from ISOxo.

11303.name: Music Kit | KILL SCRIPT, All Night
11303.desc: Are you a lover or a fighter? Perhaps both? Let the entire lobby know with the "All Night" Music Kit from KILL SCRIPT.

11304.name: Music Kit | Knock2, Make U SWEAT!
11304.desc: For players who treat every game like it's a Major Grand Final, even when there's only a few hundred CSR on the line. Bring the energy and the wins with Knock2's second Music Kit, "Make U SWEAT!".

11305.name: Music Kit | Rad Cat, Reason
11305.desc: Sometimes defusing the bomb is enough to be the round MVP. Celebrate every moment—big or small—with the "Reason" Music Kit from Rad Cat.

11306.name: Music Kit | TWERL and Ekko & Sidetrack, Under Bright Lights
11306.desc: There's no better time to come alive than when in the spotlight. Let the drum and bass anthem "Under Bright Lights" by TWERL and Ekko & Sidetrack carry you and your team to new heights.

12019.name: Container | Copenhagen 2024 Legends Sticker Capsule
12019.desc:
This capsule contains a single Copenhagen 2024 Legends participant Paper, Glitter, Holo, or Gold sticker.

50% of the proceeds from the sale of this capsule support the included organizations.

That sticker can be applied to any weapon you own and can be scraped to look more worn. You can scrape the same sticker multiple times, making it a bit more worn each time, until it is removed from the weapon.

12293.desc:
This Music Kit will replace all of the music in the game and is shareable with anyone you are playing with. It also includes an MVP Anthem that plays for everyone in the match when you are MVP.

The Music Kit replaces the following music:
- Main Menu
- Round Start and End
- Map Objective
- Ten Second Warning
- Death Camera

12294.desc: This sticker can be applied to any weapon you own and can be scraped to look more worn. You can scrape the same sticker multiple times, making it a bit more worn each time, until it is removed from the weapon.

12295.desc: This graffiti can be applied to the in-game world. You can apply it until you run out of charges.

12296.desc: This patch can be applied to any agent you own. Once applied, it can be removed but not recovered.
